full_title: The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You) by The Nat "King" Cole Trio
title: The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You)
title_with_featured: The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You)

description.plain:
This is the original version of “The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You).” With only piano, bass, and guitar as backing for Nat King Cole, it creates an intimate atmosphere.

It’s also the only version of the song to include the phrase “reindeers,” as Cole fixed the grammatical error to “reindeer” in all subsequent releases of the song. The Nat King Cole Trio would go on to rerecord the song and rerelease it within the same year with additional musical backing. They would rerelease it in 1953 and 1961 as well.

lyrics:
8 ContributorsThe Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You) LyricsThis is the original version of “The Christmas Song (Merry Christmas to You).” With only piano, bass, and guitar as backing for Nat King Cole, it creates an intimate atmosphere.
It’s also the only version of… Read More 
Chestnuts roasting on an open fire
Jack Frost nipping at your nose
Yuletide carols being sung by a choir
And folks dressed up like Eskimos
Everybody knows a turkey and some mistletoe
Help to make the season bright
Tiny tots with their eyes all aglow
Will find it hard to sleep tonight

They know that Santa's on his way
He's loaded lots of toys and goodies on his sleigh
And every mother's child is gonna spy
To see if reindeers really know how to fly

And so I'm offering this simple phrase
To kids from one to ninety-two
Although its been said many times, many ways
Merry Christmas to you


And so I'm offering this simple phrase
To kids from one to ninety-two
Although its been said many times, many ways
Merry Christmas to you
